              {
                "type": "output_text",
                "text": "To solve the equation \\(\\sin(x) + x^2 = 42\\), we can rewrite it as:\n\n\\[\nx^2 + \\sin(x) - 42 = 0\n\\]\n\nThis is a transcendental equation because it involves both algebraic and trigonometric terms. We'll need to use numerical methods to find the solutions.\n\nLet's find the real solutions numerically.",
